# Cursor Rules Overview

This directory contains organized rules for different aspects of the Voron printer configuration project.

## Rule Files

- **rules.mdc** - Repository-wide patterns and file organization
- **markdown.mdc** - Markdown formatting standards
- **gcode.mdc** - G-code, Klipper configuration, and macro creation patterns
- **python-core.mdc** - General Python coding patterns and standards
- **python-testing.mdc** - Python-specific testing patterns and pytest standards
- **python-coding-standards.mdc** - Python coding style guidelines (indentation, line length, comments)
- **logging.mdc** - Logging practices and configuration for all file types

## Usage

Each rule file applies to specific file types and directories based on the `globs` pattern. Rules marked with `alwaysApply: true` will be automatically applied to all matching files.

## Key Principles

- UPPERCASE for macro parameters
- Always use `params.PARAM_NAME` for Jinja variables
- Test data dictionary at top, clean function below
- Consistent markdown formatting
- Logical file organization

## File Coverage

- **gcode.mdc**: All `.cfg`, `.gcode`, and `.j2` files (includes macros)
- **python-core.mdc**: All `.py` files (general Python standards)
- **python-testing.mdc**: Test files (`test_*.py`, `conftest.py`)
- **python-coding-standards.mdc**: All `.py` files (coding style)
- **logging.mdc**: All `.py`, `.cfg`, and `.gcode` files (logging practices)
- **markdown.mdc**: All `.md` and `.mdc` files
- **rules.mdc**: All files (repository-wide patterns)

